<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="UTF-8">

<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

<title>CluckSafe 🐔</title>

<style>

    body {

        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;

        margin: 0;

        background: #f4f4f4;

        color: #333;

        text-align: center;

    }

    header {

        background: #ffcc00;

        padding: 20px;

    }

    h1 {

        margin: 0;

    }

    .container {

        padding: 20px;

    }

    .card {

        background: white;

        margin: 15px auto;

        padding: 20px;

        max-width: 500px;

        border-radius: 10px;

        box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);

    }

    button {

        background: #ff9900;

        border: none;

        padding: 10px 15px;

        border-radius: 5px;

        cursor: pointer;

        color: white;

    }

    .hidden {

        display: none;

        margin-top: 10px;

        text-align: left;

    }

</style>

</head>

<body>

<header>

    <h1>🐔 CluckSafe</h1>

    <p>Protect your “eggs” (your info) online!</p>

</header>

<div class="container">

    <div class="card">

        <h2>🎣 What is Phishing?</h2>

        <p>Phishing is when scammers try to trick you into giving personal info through fake emails, texts, or websites.</p>

        <button onclick="toggle('phishing')">Read More</button>

        <div id="phishing" class="hidden">

            <p><strong>Common Signs:</strong></p>

            <ul>

                <li>Urgent messages (“Act now!”)</li>

                <li>Fake links that look real</li>

                <li>Requests for passwords or money</li>

            </ul>

            <p><strong>How to Avoid:</strong></p>

            <ul>

                <li>Check the sender’s email carefully</li>

                <li>Don’t click suspicious links</li>

                <li>Use two-factor authentication</li>

            </ul>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="card">

        <h2>🪪 What is Identity Theft?</h2>

        <p>Identity theft happens when someone steals your personal information to commit fraud.</p>

        <button onclick="toggle('identity')">Read More</button>

        <div id="identity" class="hidden">

            <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>

            <ul>

                <li>Opening accounts in your name</li>

                <li>Using your credit card</li>

                <li>Filing taxes as you</li>

            </ul>

            <p><strong>How to Avoid:</strong></p>

            <ul>

                <li>Keep personal info private</li>

                <li>Monitor your bank statements</li>

                <li>Use strong, unique passwords</li>

            </ul>

        </div>

    </div>

</div>

<script>

function toggle(id) {

    var section = document.getElementById(id);

    if (section.classList.contains("hidden")) {

        section.classList.remove("hidden");

    } else {

        section.classList.add("hidden");

    }

}

</script>

</body>

</html>